        <h1 class="fw-bold">Logitech: Sim Racing for Everyone</h1>
        <p>Logitech is one of the most accessible and trusted brands in sim racing. Known for their reliable and affordable gear, Logitech has introduced millions of gamers to the world of racing simulation. Their G series wheel and pedal sets are a staple in beginner and casual sim racing setups, offering a solid balance of performance, simplicity, and price.</p>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">Iconic Racing Wheels</h2>
        <p>Logitech’s sim racing legacy is defined by its popular racing wheels, built to bring realism and immersion to console and PC users alike.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>G29 & G920</strong> – Belt-driven wheels with dual-motor force feedback</li>
            <li><strong>G923</strong> – Upgraded with TRUEFORCE haptic feedback for greater realism</li>
            <li>Compatible with PC, PlayStation, and Xbox (model-dependent)</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">TRUEFORCE Technology</h2>
        <p>With the G923, Logitech introduced TRUEFORCE—a more advanced force feedback system that interacts directly with in-game physics and audio engines for more responsive, detailed sensations.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Higher fidelity feedback compared to previous G series wheels</li>
            <li>More dynamic road feel and car behavior through the wheel</li>
            <li>Improved immersion for supported racing titles</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">Reliable Pedal Sets</h2>
        <p>Logitech pedal sets are durable and easy to use, perfect for beginners or casual players. The G923 comes with a redesigned brake pedal for a more realistic feel.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Three-pedal layout: throttle, brake, and clutch</li>
            <li>Progressive resistance on brake pedal</li>
            <li>Compatible with most sim racing cockpits and stands</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">Logitech Software & Compatibility</h2>
        <p>Logitech wheels are easy to set up and configure, thanks to user-friendly software and wide game support.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>G HUB software for customization and updates</li>
            <li>Works with almost all major sim racing titles</li>
            <li>Plug-and-play support for consoles and PC</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">Affordable Sim Racing Entry Point</h2>
        <p>Logitech makes sim racing accessible to more people by offering complete kits at budget-friendly prices—without sacrificing build quality or long-term reliability.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Great for beginners and casual sim racers</li>
            <li>Long-lasting, low-maintenance hardware</li>
            <li>Wide community support and aftermarket mods available</li>
        </ul>
        <br>
        <hr>

        <h2 class="text-decoration-underline">Why Choose Logitech?</h2>
        <p>Logitech is perfect for those getting into sim racing. It’s easy to set up, fun to use, and backed by a reputation for reliability across gaming peripherals.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Affordable all-in-one racing wheel and pedal bundles</li>
            <li>Great performance-to-price ratio</li>
            <li>Ideal stepping stone to higher-end gear</li>
        </ul>
